SELECT - used to retreive the data from a table and display it
**BASIC SYNTAX**
         SELECT Col_Name,
         FROM Table_Name;
ex- Q-SELECT ALL THE COLUMNS FROM THE EMP TABLE 
    A-    SELECT *                   
          FROM EMP;
    Q-SELECT ONLY EMPLOYEE NAMES FROM THE EMP TABLE
    A-    SELECT ENAME
          FROM EMP;
NOTE-
  - * = selects all the columns/details of the table and displays it.
  - ENAME= only selects the employee names column of the table and displays it.
